  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Service Coordination, Emergency Preparedness and Response, and Improvement of Living Conditions of Rohingya in Cox&apos;s Bazar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at contributing to the strengthening of coordination of services and to enhance the overall living conditions of the Rohingya population in Cox&apos;s Bazar (Bangladesh). IOM strengthened coordination will ensure equitable and appropriate delivery of humanitarian aid in Kutupalong-Balukhali Expansion Site and Teknaf displacement sites. Additionally, IOM is undertaking site improvement works, increasing access of the population to humanitarian services and decreasing the physical safety risks, including risks of exposure to gender-based violence. Through this project, IOM is also strengthening the accountability to the affected populations through Communication with Communities programming, as well as strengthening the capacity of humanitarian service providers, the local government and other actors. IOM will also strengthen community-based disaster risk reduction programming.</narrative>
  </description>
